  "body": "Hi ,\r\nI am running geth node on a pretty robust server with lots of disk space, memory and processor (screenshot attached). Once geth fully syncs and I connect mist wallet to it it shows the latest blocks and number of peers all that. Next time I try to connect it shows at 6000-8000 blocks behind and need to wait and dont get the latest txs. Right now, it would never catch up with the latest blocks. There is not error/warning in geth console. How can I keep geth syching upto date? Its running 24*7*365\r\nI remember it happened with way early version of geth too almost a year ago..so definitely its not related to this particular version.\r\n![capture](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/28849607/33234097-ca2a5c6e-d1ee-11e7-97c9-40f46bcf6168.PNG)\r\n![geth](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/28849607/33234100-d2ffad6c-d1ee-11e7-84ff-b863505e8dc5.PNG)\r\n\r\n\r\n#### System information\r\nGeth\r\nVersion: 1.7.2-stable\r\nGit Commit: 1db4ecdc0b9e828ff65777fb466fc7c1d04e0de9\r\nArchitecture: amd64\r\nProtocol Versions: [63 62]\r\nNetwork Id: 1\r\nGo Version: go1.9\r\nOperating System: windows\r\nGOPATH=\r\nGOROOT=c:\\go\r\n#### Expected behaviour\r\nonce fully snitched, it should be able to keep up with latest blocks\r\n\r\n#### Actual behaviour\r\nsynching keeps falling 6000-8000 block behind.\r\n\r\n#### Steps to reproduce the behaviour\r\nlet geth run and connect mist/eth wallet to it. Once it shows blocks are fully synced, in next hours/days it falls way behind on its own? \r\n\r\n#### Backtrace\r\n\r\n````\r\n[backtrace]\r\n````\r\n",
