    "body": "Geth get stuck and being very slow to sync 1 minute for a block after a fast sync. See logs\r\n```\r\nINFO [01-02|21:11:08] Imported new chain segment               blocks=1 txs=130 mgas=5.224 elapsed=1m28.520s mgasps=0.059 number=4590436 hash=932055‚Ä¶e8f55b\r\nINFO [01-02|21:11:09] Imported new chain segment               blocks=1 txs=1   mgas=0.021 elapsed=488.803ms mgasps=0.043 number=4590437 hash=bb8b52‚Ä¶cd6bdd\r\nINFO [01-02|21:11:17] Imported new chain segment               blocks=1 txs=4   mgas=0.204 elapsed=8.520s    mgasps=0.024 number=4590438 hash=a974fb‚Ä¶098550\r\nINFO [01-02|21:12:06] Imported new chain segment               blocks=1 txs=81  mgas=2.707 elapsed=48.988s   mgasps=0.055 number=4590439 hash=419676‚Ä¶16823d\r\n```\r\nI 'm currently using `Geth/v1.7.3-stable-4bb3c89d/linux-amd64/go1.9.2`. Nothing appear in logs with verbosity 3.\r\nAfter a little of investigation, geth ask for 192 blocks of data but lot of peers respond with ` Peer discarded announcement` after the request. Geth get stuck on sync and the distance with the last block continue to grow :-(",
