    "body": "Geth fails to stay in sync...as soon as it syncs.\r\n\r\n#### System information\r\n\r\nGeth version: `1.8.6`\r\nOS & Version: Ubuntu 16.04\r\nHardware: AWS t.medium 4GB 2 core 1TB SSD\r\n\r\n#### Expected behaviour\r\n\r\nGeth remains synced to network.\r\n\r\n#### Actual behaviour\r\n\r\nAs soon as sync is complete, i.e., `eth.syncing == false`, synchronization fails. The local chain can fall behind by as much as 200 blocks. Checking the log reveals multiple peers being dropped:\r\n\r\n```\r\n[04-23|18:52:21] Synchronisation failed, retrying         err=\"block download canceled (requested)\"\r\nApr 23 18:52:39 ip-xxx-xx-xx-xx geth[21609]: WARN [04-23|18:52:39] Synchronisation failed, dropping peer\"\r\n```\r\n\r\n\"Synchronisation failed, dropping peer\" occurs up to 8 times before my client begins to import new chain segments again. The `eth.syncing.highestBlock` fails to update its value during the resync process.\r\n\r\n#### Steps to reproduce the behaviour\r\n\r\nRun geth. Intermittent.\r\n\r\n",
